rder policies, a linked chain spanning the heart of U.S. imperialism. This highly original and beautifully wrought book unveils how the transcontinental railroad laid the tracks of the U.S. Empire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCapitalismzUnited Statesy19th century. 0aChinesezUnited StatesxEconomic conditionsy19th century. 0aColonization. 0aImperialism. 0aIndians of North AmericazUnited StatesxEconomic conditionsy19th century. 0aRailroadszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aRailroadszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aasian american histories.  abusiness records.  acapitalism.  acheyenne.  achinese migrants.  acolonialism.  aexclusionary border policies.  aimperial foundations.  aindigenous.  ainterdisciplinary study.  alakota.  alegislative.  amilitary occupation.  amilitary.  apawnee native american tribes.  atranscontinental railroad.  aus imperialism.  aus political economy.  aviolent global histories.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969056zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969056423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/97805